"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is using 'sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)' which is incorrect because set_context() function does not have an 'rc' argument. It should be used with one of its built-in contexts or with a dictionary of parameters that define the scaling. Also, 'sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)' is incorrect because the parameters in the style_dict are not part of the style definition. To customize the seaborn styles with any matplotlib parameters, set_theme() function should be used.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5,6\\n< scale_dict = {\\n<     'grid.linewidth': 4\\n---\\n> scale_dict = {'paper': 1}\\n> style_dict = {\\n>     'axes.grid': True,\\n>     'grid.color': 'red',\\n>     'grid.linewidth': 4\\n8c9\\n< sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_context(**scale_dict)\\n14c15\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_theme(rc=style_dict)\\n\"\n}"